if you think I'm pleased...

08:25.572 --> 08:28.063
the two of us are standing here
arguing about this.

08:29.309 --> 08:32.369
You asked me.
I'm telling you how I feel.

08:32.445 --> 08:37.405
What? What? What? Am I sensing
a tension in the atmosphere here?

08:37.482 --> 08:41.783
We're fine.
Let's go to work.

08:56.803 --> 08:58.737
Here you go. Sit down.

09:04.477 --> 09:06.775
- What's this?
- You got a minute?

09:10.550 --> 09:13.519
I play basketball
with this guy twice a week.

09:13.586 --> 09:16.146
He's a buddy of mine.

09:16.222 --> 09:20.818
He and another guy got into a beef.
The other guy is kind of a jerk.

09:20.893 --> 09:23.293
Getting
in Nathan's face, pushing,

09:23.363 --> 09:25.388
and Nathan tried
to walk away,

09:25.465 --> 09:27.695
but the guy wouldn't
give him any room.

09:27.767 --> 09:30.702
Finally Nathan takes a slug at him
and the guy goes down, dead.

09:32.071 --> 09:34.301
- What's his story?
- He's a good citizen.

09:34.374 --> 09:36.342
He got in some trouble
when he was a kid, 18, 19...

09:36.409 --> 09:40.072
- What kind of trouble?
- It was a marijuana charge and failure to appear.

09:40.146 --> 09:42.171
He did six months.
But he's clean, Lieutenant.

09:42.248 --> 09:45.217
He's a mail carrier.
He's a good guy.

09:45.285 --> 09:47.014
A family man.

09:47.086 --> 09:49.782
So I read him his rights.
He's a little shook up.

09:49.856 --> 09:52.552
But I think somebody else
should be assigned.

09:52.625 --> 09:56.083
- Medavoy's up. I'll fill him in.
- I just need a minute with him.

10:00.300 --> 10:02.860
- I can't do this. I can't go to jail.
- I know.

10:02.935 --> 10:05.495
I'll do my best
to make it easy on you.

10:05.571 --> 10:08.301
But we gotta take a few steps here.
D.A.'s gotta look into this.

10:08.374 --> 10:10.934
- We got... What?
- This is Detective Medavoy.

10:11.010 --> 10:14.241
He's gonna handle the case
because I'm a witness.

10:14.314 --> 10:16.407
So you wanna make a statement,
you give it to him.

10:16.482 --> 10:19.042
I'm not gonna make any statement.
I'm not gonna do anything.

10:19.118 --> 10:21.712
- I have to write up a statement.
- Well, what about me, man?

10:21.788 --> 10:26.122
You're gonna be here for awhile
until the D.A. Decides what to do.

10:26.192 --> 10:29.218
I'll put you in an interview room
while we interview the witnesses.

10:29.295 --> 10:31.923
- You gonna lock me up?
- In an interview room.

10:31.998 --> 10:35.024
But he'll be able to change his clothes
in there, get coffee?

10:35.101 --> 10:36.534
Yeah.

10:36.602 --> 10:42.040
- You're gonna lock me up?
- I gotta, man. I gotta lock you up.

10:44.177 --> 10:46.611
Go ahead.

10:46.679 --> 10:48.613
- I'll talk to you later.
- Sure you will.

11:06.532 --> 11:10.366
John, we got a homicide
in F.D.R. At Pearl Street.

11:10.436 --> 11:12.370
You want me
to grab Martinez?

11:12.438 --> 11:14.463
Nah. Let mejust get
some clothes.

11:14.540 --> 11:17.998
Listen. Did you get
squared away on your buddy?

11:18.077 --> 11:20.944
Yeah.
I gave it to Medavoy.

11:21.013 --> 11:23.413
Look at this.
I'm ankle deep in water over here.

11:23.483 --> 11:28.546
